question: This travels around the world but stays in one spot? What is it?
If I drink, I die. If I eat, I am fine. What am I?
It is higher without the head, than with it. What is it?
Where does Friday come before Thursday?
I am a word. If you pronounce me rightly, it will be wrong. If you pronounce me wrong it is right? What word am I?
What belongs to you but others use it more than you do?
I am taken from a mine and shut up in a wooden case, from which I am never released, and yet I am used by almost everybody. What am I?
The first man is the master of priceless gems; The second man is the master of love; The third man is the master of shovels; The fourth man is the master of big sticks; Who are they?
